' PlantUML example — Implementation layer: internal steps behind a single
' BPMN task, TASK-ERASE-ACTIVE, from the GDPR erasure process.
'
' Derived from:
'   - canon/views/bpmn/data-subject-erasure.bpmn.transitrix.yaml
'       TASK-LOCATE "Locate personal data across systems"
'       TASK-ERASE-ACTIVE "Erase from active OMS & CRM"
'       GW-ARCHIVE "Personal data in cold-storage archive?"
'       TASK-FLAG-GAP "Flag archive exception for manual review"
'
' Not a duplicate of the BPMN view: the BPMN shows the business task flow
' across lanes (Support / DPO / Ops) at task granularity. This activity
' diagram decomposes one of those tasks (TASK-LOCATE -> TASK-ERASE-ACTIVE)
' into the engineering steps OMS actually performs — detail below what a
' business-process lane is meant to carry.

!include transitrix-theme.puml
@startuml Erasure sweep — implementation detail

start
:Query active orders for data-subject ID;
:Query CRM contact record for data-subject ID;
note right: TASK-LOCATE

partition "TASK-ERASE-ACTIVE" #f4f9fb {
  :Soft-delete PII fields on active orders (OMS DB);
  :Soft-delete contact PII fields (CRM, via REST outbound);
  :Propagate erasure event OMS -> CRM;
}

if (Personal data in cold-storage archive?) then (yes)
  :Flag archive exception for manual review;
  note right: TASK-FLAG-GAP — known gap, see NOTATIONS_AUDIT / ASSERTION-ECOMM-GDPR-ERASURE-1
else (no)
endif

:Join erasure path (GW-CONFIRM-JOIN);
stop

@enduml
